40|$|The {{progress}} made in diagnostic and therapeutic medicine {{has resulted in}} {{an increase in the number}} of malpractice suits brought against medical practitioners. To constitute negligence it must be shown that the conduct of the accused did not measure up to the standard of care the law required of him in the particular circumstances and that he acted with guilt and therefore can be blamed for the deed. This paper describes <b>medical</b> practitioner <b>negligence</b> and reviews relevant cases...|$|R
