50|$|This {{initiative}} {{will require}} the regular drug and alcohol testing of doctors. Administration {{of this will be}} given to the California Medical Board. Doctors will also be required to report any other doctor suspected of being under the influence while on duty. In addition, doctors will be required to check the states CURES (Controlled Substance Utilization Review and Evaluation System) prescription drug history database before prescribing certain controlled substances to patients. Furthermore, the $250,000 cap on pain and suffering damages in <b>medical</b> <b>negligence</b> lawsuits will be increased to account for inflation. Supporters argued that this will reduce <b>medical</b> <b>negligence,</b> while opponents were concerned that the cap increase in <b>medical</b> <b>negligence</b> lawsuits will eventually lead to higher health care costs.|$|E
